               <msContents>
                  <summary>Four Gospels F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-12v: Introduction to the Four Gospels.  F<locus target="#13r">13r, </locus>-16r: Eusebian Canon Tables. F<locus target="#16rv">16rv, </locus>: Table of Contents for the Gospel of Matthew. F<locus target="#17rv">17rv, </locus>: on the Resurrection. F<locus target="#18r">18r, </locus>-72r: Gospel of Matthew. F<locus target="#72v">72v, </locus>: Introduction to the Gospel of Mark. <locus target="#73r">73r, </locus>: Table of Contents to the Gospel of Mark. F<locus target="#74r">74r, </locus>-105r: The Gospel of Mark. <locus target="#105v">105v, </locus>: Introduction to the Gospel of Luke.  F<locus target="#106r">106r, </locus>-166r: The Gospel of Luke.  The text of the gospels includes the canon numbers in the margins as well as indications of quotations from the Old Testament.  F<locus target="#166v">166v, </locus>-167r: Introduction to the Gospel of John. F<locus target="#167rv">167rv, </locus>: Table of Contents for the Gospel of John. F<locus target="#168r">168r, </locus>-215r: The Gospel of John. Notes: f. i r and v v: On the importance of fasting. Ff. ii r-iv r: Excerpt from Book of the Wise, መጽሐፈ፡ ጠቢባን፡, a collection of wisdom sayings. <locus target="#166v">166v, </locus> includes a mention of the owner, ዘጊዮርጊስ. <locus target="#216v">216v</locus>: Record of the sale of the downstairs of a house by አቤቶ አሞኔዎስ to ወዘሮ ወለተ ገብርኤል who sold it to አቤቶ ዮሐንስ. A huge list of witnesses is included. The names and the use of the language indicate an origin in Tigre.</summary>
